IN - pass input values to a stored procedure. These parameters are read-only within the procedure
(counterpart is argument)
Example: Passing an employee ID to retrieve specific employee details

OUT - return a value from the stored procedure. The procedure can modify the value of an OUT parameter
(counterpart is return value)
Example: Calculating the total number of employees and returning it as an OUT parameter

INOUT - pass value to the procedure and also retrieve a modified value
Example: Passing an initial balance and updating it based on transactions